20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrossroads-school-and-startups-2013-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECrossroads%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20fall%20of%20seventh%20grade%20before%20graduating%20in%20June%202023.%20The%20school%20has%20grades%20K-12%20and%20is%20currently%20ranked%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.niche.com%2Fk12%2Fsearch%2Fbest-schools-for-the-arts%2Fs%2Fcalifornia%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E11th-best%20school%20for%20the%20arts%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20California%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.niche.com%2Fk12%2Fsearch%2Fbest-schools-for-the-arts%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E28th-best%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20nation.%20This%20ranking%20seems%20appropriate%20to%20me%20%E2%80%94%20its%20creative%20teaching%20approach%20sets%20it%20apart%20from%20other%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20liked%20Crossroads'%20emphasis%20on%20giving%20students%20space%20to%20grow%20and%20explore%20interests%20outside%20of%20school.%20Every%20senior%20student%20got%20three%20weeks%20off%20to%20pursue%20a%20personal%20development%20project%2C%20for%20example%2C%20and%20many%20students%20learned%20new%20skills%20like%20cooking%2C%20sewing%2C%20speaking%20a%20new%20language%2C%20or%20building%20structures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EStudents%20were%20very%20aware%20of%20who%20the%20famous%20parents%20were%20%E2%80%94%20and%20not%20every%20student%20was%20rich%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECrossroads%20says%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.xrds.org%2Fadmission-and-affordability%2Faffording-crossroads%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eone%20in%20four%20students%20receives%20its%20affordability%20grant.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20kids%20on%20financial%20aid%20didn't%20really%20stick%20out%20from%20their%20peers%2C%20and%20everyone%20was%20treated%20the%20same%20way%2C%20from%20what%20I%20could%20tell.%20I%20actually%20felt%20like%20most%20people%20didn't%20know%20who%20was%20rich%20or%20not%20%E2%80%94%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmegxit-where-harry-meghan-could-send-archie-school-education-canada-2020-3%23the-family-reportedly-left-vancouver-island-for-los-angeles-before-the-canadian-border-closed-amid-the-coronavirus-outbreak-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%20a%20majority%20of%20kids%20at%20Crossroads%20were%20rich%2C%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20they%20didn't%20flaunt%20it%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20and%20they%20were%20treated%20the%20same%20as%20everyone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20everyone%20knew%20if%20someone's%20parents%20were%20famous%20%E2%80%94%20most%20people%20found%20out%20by%20word%20of%20mouth.%20Even%20then%2C%20they%20were%20still%20treated%20the%20same%2C%20for%20the%20most%20part.%20Famous%20parents%20weren't%20really%20seen%20roaming%20the%20campus%2C%20but%20they%20were%20definitely%20involved%20and%20a%20part%20of%20the%20school.%20It%20was%20pretty%20common%20to%20see%20some%20of%20them%20at%20our%20basketball%20games%20or%20other%20large%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20wasn't%20a%20sense%20of%20entitlement%20among%20students%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20had%20their%20own%20sense%20of%20fashion%20and%20style.%20Most%20kids%20either%20wore%20street-wear%20vintage-ish%20clothing%2C%20or%20total%20designer%20clothing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20a%20lot%20of%20students%20driving%20Teslas%2C%20and%20while%20most%20of%20the%20cars%20were%20pretty%20nice%20like%20BMWs%20and%20Audis%2C%20nothing%20was%20too%20crazy%20compared%20to%20other%20private%20schools.%20Overall%2C%20I%20found%20that%20the%20students%20were%20pretty%20down-to-earth%20and%20not%20super%20competitive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20Crossroads%20students%20and%20alums%20feel%20like%20the%20school%20and%20its%20network%20open%20doors%2C%20but%20it%20depends%20on%20the%20industry.%20For%20example%2C%20students%20benefit%20from%20an%20extensive%20alumni%20network%20in%20film%20and%20TV.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOutsiders%20think%20that%20Crossroads%20kids%20are%20artsy%20and%20not%20that%20bright%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that's%20not%20entirely%20true%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20placement%20into%20prestigious%20universities%2C%20in%20my%20class%2C%20we%20had%20around%2020%20kids%20get%20into%20Ivy%20League%20schools%20or%20equivalent%20institutions%2C%20which%20was%20over%2010%25%20of%20our%20grade.%20And%2C%20most%20of%20the%20kids%20who%20didn't%20go%20to%20Ivy%20Leagues%20still%20went%20to%20their%20top-choice%20colleges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20will%20say%2C%20though%2C%20that%20it%20was%20rare%20to%20find%20a%20true%20go-getter%20at%20Crossroads.%20From%20what%20I've%20gathered%2C%20some%20students%20chose%20the%20school%20to%20capitalize%20on%20its%20lenient%20academic%20requirements.%20For%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.collegetransitions.com%2Fblog%2Fprivate-schools%2Fcrossroads-school-for-arts-sciences-los-angeles%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAcademic%2520Highlights%253A%2520The%2520school%2520replaced%2Ccumulative%2520GPA%2520or%2520class%2520rank.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECrossroads%20replaced%20AP%20courses%20with%20Crossroads%20Advanced%20Studies%20(CAS)%20classes%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20I%20think%20are%20easier%20than%20AP%20classes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20were%20other%20kids%20who%20took%20advantage%20of%20this%20relaxed%20school%20environment%20to%20explore%20their%20own%20interests%20and%20educate%20themselves%20outside%20of%20school.%20There%20were%20a%20handful%20of%20students%20who%20took%20hours%20of%20art%20classes%20per%20day%2C%20but%20that's%20far%20from%20the%20majority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20this%20is%20why%20there%20were%20a%20lot%20of%20students%20who%20put%20in%20minimal%20effort%20into%20their%20academics%20but%20got%20accepted%20to%20top%20colleges%20%E2%80%94%20they%20used%20the%20extra%20time%20they%20had%20to%20pursue%20extracurricular%20activities%20that%20enhanced%20their%20college%20applications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20feel%20behind%20in%20college%20because%20Crossroads%20didn't%20offer%20AP%20classes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20now%20a%20first%20year%20student%20at%20Duke%20University%20studying%20public%20policy%20with%20an%20expected%20certificate%20in%20markets%20and%20management%2C%20but%20I%20feel%20like%20I'm%20running%20behind.%20I'm%20multiple%20credits%20behind%20my%20peers%20because%20I'm%20stuck%20taking%20classes%20they%20don't%20need%20to%20take.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20didn't%20have%20%3Cem%3Ereal%20%3C%2Fem%3Efinals%20at%20Crossroads%2C%20as%20in%20the%20tests%20that%20make%20up%20a%20stupidly%20large%20portion%20of%20your%20grade%20like%20most%20high%20schools%20have.%20We%20did%20have%20bigger%20tests%20and%20projects%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20semesters%2C%20but%20they%20weren't%20worth%20the%20majority%20of%20our%20grade%2C%20which%20helped%20relieve%20stress%20and%20make%20the%20academics%20feel%20less%20demanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20students%20cheated%20at%20Crossroads%20(which%2C%20I%20could%20imagine%2C%20is%20common%20at%20most%20schools).%20I%20can%20name%20a%20handful%20of%20times%20when%20teachers%20singled%20out%20one%20student%20for%20slightly%20suspicious%20behavior.%20From%20the%20kids%20I%20know%20who%20were%20accused%20of%20cheating%2C%20their%20parents%20were%20contacted%20multiple%20times%20and%20they%20usually%20faced%20a%20harsh%20grade%20drop%20in%20the%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20from%20what%20I%20saw%20in%20my%20own%20classes%2C%20most%20teachers%20didn't%20go%20out%20of%20their%20way%20to%20catch%20students%20cheating.%20If%20a%20teacher%20did%20try%2C%20it%20was%20usually%20based%20on%20the%20school's%20protocols%20and%20not%20their%20own%20personal%20desires%20to%20mess%20with%20students.%20I%20feel%20like%20this%20trusting%20relationship%20made%20the%20school%20environment%20a%20lot%20more%20relaxed%20and%20actually%20led%20to%20less%20cheating%20overall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20best%20thing%20about%20Crossroads%20was%20that%20it%20allowed%20me%20to%20explore%20many%20of%20my%20interests%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20moved%20up%20grade%20levels%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20take%20some%20interesting%20and%20niche%20classes%2C%20like%20a%20history%20of%20American%20film%20class%20and%20a%20literature%20through%20horror%20stories%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20I%20feel%20that%20Crossroads%20takes%20a%20unique%20approach%20to%20teaching%2C%20but%20it%20may%20not%20be%20for%20everyone.%20I%20enjoyed%20my%20experience%20because%20it%20allowed%20me%20to%20really%20diversify%20myself%20and%20explore%20my%20passions%20in%20high%20school%20%E2%80%94%20I%20likely%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20able%20to%20do%20that%20otherwise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ECrossroads%20School%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EIf%20you%20attended%20a%20prestigious%20school%20and%20would%20like%20to%20share%20your%20story%2C%20email%20Aria%20Yang%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aayang%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eayang%40insider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrossroads-school-arts-sciences-santa-monica-california-student-experience-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701947341000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656f980e7a3c8094d5d9eb06%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrossroads-school-arts-sciences-santa-monica-california-student-experience-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Cross