20have%20fared%20better%20in%20this%20same%20situation%2C%20one%20expert%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20hoped%20its%20big%20counteroffensive%20punch%20would%20hit%20like%20an%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-almost-ready-counteroffensive-iron-fist-western-weapons-russia-2023-4%5C%22%3Eiron%20fist%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20instead%20things%20went%20sideways%20from%20the%20start%2C%20possibly%20even%20before%20it%20began.%20It%20drew%20blood%2C%20but%20it%20didn't%20break%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20war%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20far%20from%20over%2C%20making%20it%20critical%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20went%20wrong%20if%20Ukraine%20hopes%20to%20defeat%20the%20Russians%20and%20drive%20them%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKyiv%20launched%20its%20counteroffensive%20against%20Russian%20forces%20in%20June%2C%20months%20later%20than%20expected.%20Its%20publicly%20stated%20objectives%20were%20ambitious%20and%20certain%20to%20test%20the%20abilities%20of%20their%20forces%20against%20Russia's%20formidable%20layered%20defenses.%20But%20the%20plan%20didn't%20work%20out.%20Six%20months%20later%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20not%20achieved%20the%20sweeping%20territorial%20gains%20it%20sought%2C%20and%20it%20is%20unlikely%20to%20do%20so%2C%20Ukrainian%20officials%20have%20acknowledged.%20The%20Ukrainian%20counteroffensive%2C%20at%20this%20point%2C%20is%20basically%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problems%2C%20some%20of%20the%20war's%20more%20influential%20watchers%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20were%20complicated%20and%20compounded.%20Ukraine%20and%20the%20West%20attempted%20to%20give%20mostly%20inexperienced%20troops%20a%20crash%20course%20in%20new%20weapons%20and%20tried%20to%20radically%20change%20how%20its%20military%20fights%20in%20a%20few%20months%20to%20pursue%20unrealistic%20expectations%20in%20the%20face%20of%20Russian%20defenses%20that%20became%20impassable%20kill%20zones%20of%20mines%20and%20drones%2C%20raked%20by%20artillery%2C%20for%20even%20advanced%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20counteroffensive%20push%20was%20in%20the%20Zaporizhzhia%20Oblast%20in%20southern%20Ukraine.%20That%20approach%20aimed%20to%20cut%20down%20from%20Orikhiv%2C%20east%20of%20the%20bend%20of%20the%20Dnipro%20River%3Cstrong%3E%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20and%20toward%20Melitopol%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20divide%20Russian%20forces%20near%20the%20Sea%20of%20Azov.%20There%20were%20other%20axes%20as%20well%2C%20such%20as%20an%20offensive%20east%20towards%20Russian-occupied%20Donetsk%20and%20another%20outside%20of%20Bakhmut.%20More%20recently%2C%20Ukraine%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-fighting-hard-across-a-key-river-to-reignite-counteroffensive-2023-11%5C%22%3Eestablished%20a%20foothold%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20eastern%20bank%20of%20the%20Dnipro.%20It%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20what%20Ukraine%20will%20achieve%20there%2C%20but%20experts%20have%20limited%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%2C%20reports%20say%2C%20has%20only%20taken%20200%20square%20miles%20of%20territory%20this%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22618%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Assessed%20control%20of%20terrain%20around%20Zaporizhzhia%20as%20of%20September%2021%2C%202023%2C%20courtesy%20of%20the%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6570e27b7a3c8094d5da6a89%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22814%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAssessed%20control%20of%20terrain%20around%20Zaporizhzhia%20as%20of%20September%2021%2C%202023%2C%20courtesy%20of%20the%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War.%3Cp%3EInstitute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War%20and%20AEI's%20Critical%20Threats%20Project%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20counteroffensive's%20progress%20has%20been%20slow%20since%20the%20beginning%2C%20which%20was%20acknowledged%20by%20officials%2C%20including%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%2C%20just%20weeks%20into%20the%20operation.%C2%A0A%20number%20of%20different%20things%20needed%20to%20go%20right%20that%20simply%20did%20not.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFranz-Stefan%20Gady%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20International%20Institute%20for%20Strategic%20Studies%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he%20believes%20that%20the%20counteroffensive%2C%20%26quot%3Bunder%20the%20right%20circumstances%2C%20with%20a%20more%20strategic%20approach%20to%20training%20and%20understanding%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20Armed%20Forces%2C%20what%20they%20need%2C%20and%20what%20is%20required%20by%20Western%20military%20instructors%20and%20others%2C%20would%20have%20made%20a%20difference.%26quot%3B%20All%20the%20pieces%20didn't%20quite%20fall%20into%20place%20though.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20not%20the%20end%20of%20the%20discussion.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20campaign%20fails%20or%20it%20doesn't%20meet%20its%20objectives%2C%20then%20there's%20learning%20opportunities%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20George%20Barros%2C%20an%20analyst%20at%20the%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20So%20the%20question%20is%3A%20how%20did%20the%20counteroffensive%20run%20into%20trouble%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EProblems%20from%20the%20start%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20aerial%20view%20shows%20smoke%20rising%20from%20a%20%20damaged%20and%20burning%20high-rise%20building%20in%20Bakhmut%2C%20April%2026%2C%202023.%20A%20mural%20showing%20a%20happy%20man%20with%20a%20boy%20on%20his%20shoulders%20is%20painted%20on%20one%20side.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6560dac59c7d23cb3b9f6ef5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22747%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESmoke%20rising%20from%20high-rise%20buildings%20in%20Bakhmut%2C%20April%2026%2C%202023.%3Cp%3ELibkos%2FAP%20Photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBakhmut%2C%20the%20bloodiest%20battle%20of%20the%20war%20so%20far%2C%20was%20a%20defining%20fight%20in%20the%20lead%20up%20to%20the%20counteroffensive%2C%20setting%20battlefield%20conditions%20heading%20into%20the%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20March%202023%2C%20when%20Ukrainian%20forces%20became%20practically%20encircled%20in%20the%20city%2C%20facing%20high%20casualties%20and%20dwindling%20ammo%2C%20calls%20from%20both%20home%20and%20abroad%20for%20a%20retreat%20grew%20louder.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20Zelenskyy%20dug%20his%20heels%20in%2C%20insisting%20Ukrainian%20forces%20remain%20there%20to%20deplete%20the%20waves%20of%20mercenaries%20and%20convicts%20Russia%20threw%20into%20the%20fight.%20Although%20the%20Russians%20took%20heavy%20losses%2C%20forces%20fighting%20for%20Moscow%20captured%20Bakhmut%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20war%20experts%20argue%20that%20the%20Ukrainian%20decision%20to%20stay%20in%20Bakhmut%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-fight-bakhmut-russia-wagner-forces-costly-clearly-paid-off-2023-11%5C%22%3Ewas%20worth%20it%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20given%20Russian%20losses%20and%20the%20ultimate%20destruction%20of%20the%20paramilitary%20Wagner%20Group%20and%20its%20leader%2C%20Yevgeny%20Prigozhin%2C%20who%20said%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pbs.org%2Fnewshour%2Fworld%2Fhead-of-russian-private-army-says-more-than-20000-fighters-died-in-bakhmut-battle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E20%2C000%20Russian%20forces%3C%2Fa%3E%20died%20in%20this%20effort.%20Others%20argue%20Russia%20sacrificed%20what%20it%20could%20afford%20to%20lose%2C%20such%20as%20inexperienced%20conscripts%20and%20felons%2C%20and%20forced%20Ukraine%20to%20exhaust%20some%20of%20its%20better%20troops.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20question%20is%2C%20at%20what%20point%20do%20these%20attrition%20ratios%20only%20tell%20one%20side%20of%20the%20story%20when%20you%20look%20at%20the%20relative%20quality%20of%20troops%20that%20were%20attrited%20in%20Bakhmut%2C%20when%20you%20juxtapose%20very%20experienced%20people%20dying%20and%20being%20wounded%20in%20Bakhmut%20on%20the%20Ukrainian%20side%20versus%20conscripts%20and%20felons%2C%20relatively%20inexperienced%20and%20relatively%20combat%20ineffective%20soldiers%20on%20the%20Russian%20side%20being%20killed%20and%20wounded%20during%20the%20fight%2C%26quot%3B%20Gady%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukrainian%20soldiers%20fire%20an%20AZP%20S-60%20from%20between%20trees%20near%20Bakhmut%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6560b13b9c7d23cb3b9f5ff3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMembers%20of%20Ukraine's%2056th%20Brigade%20fire%20an%20AZP%20S-60%20near%20Bakhmut%20on%20November%2010%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EKostya%20Liberov%2FLibkos%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20to%20stay%20and%20hold%20the%20line%20in%20Bakhmut%20pinned%20some%20of%20Ukraine's%20best%20troops%2C%20such%20as%20the%2024th%20Mechanized%20Brigade%20and%2080th%20Air%20Assault%20Brigade%2C%20down%20during%20planning%20stages%20for%20the%20counteroffensive%20and%20over%20the%20summer%2C%20leaving%20the%20daunting%20task%20of%20shattering%20Russian%20defenses%20to%20much%20less%20experienced%20troops%2C%20such%20as%20the%20majority%20of%20the%2047th%20Mechanized%20Brigade%2C%20roughly%2070%20percent%20of%20which%20had%20no%20prior%20combat%20experience%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2F12%2F04%2Fukraine-counteroffensive-us-planning-russia-war%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20in%20the%20counteroffensive%2C%20well-equipped%20but%20inexperienced%20units%20took%20part%20in%20concentrated%2C%20breakneck%20attacks%20on%20Russian%20lines%20but%20quickly%20ran%20into%20tough%20defenses.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmistakes-cost-