hat%20demanded%20dowry.%20But%20the%2026-year-old%20doctor%20was%20certain%20that%20she%20had%20chosen%20a%20%26quot%3Bgood%20man%26quot%3B.%20Jasim%20had%20agreed%20to%20support%20the%20match%2C%20only%20for%20his%20sister's%20happiness.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fsouth%2Fkerala-doctor-shahana-suicide-he-didnt-stand-by-her-doctors-brother-on-how-dowry-demand-crushed-her-4642268%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fsouth%2Fkerala-doctor-shahana-suicide-he-didnt-stand-by-her-doctors-brother-on-how-dowry-demand-crushed-her-4642268%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fsouth%2Fkerala-doctor-shahana-suicide-he-didnt-stand-by-her-doctors-brother-on-how-dowry-demand-crushed-her-4642268%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20the%20former%20Microsoft%20VP%20of%20HR.%20Here's%20what%20I%20would%20do%20in%20the%20first%2048%20hours%20of%20being%20laid%20off%20from%20a%20job.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223553%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22451038355%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6570f6170ec98e92f74cf73e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224681%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChris%20Williams%20writes%20that%20you%20should%20consider%20pushing%20back%20against%20a%20layoff.%3Cp%3EMHJ%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EChris%20Williams%20is%20a%20former%20Microsoft%20VP%20of%20HR%20and%20a%20podcaster%2C%20consultant%2C%20and%20TikTok%20creator.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EHe%20writes%20that%20you%20shouldn't%20sign%20a%20layoff%20package%20as%20soon%20as%20they%20offer%20it%20to%20you.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EWilliams%20also%20writes%20that%20you%20should%20consider%20pushing%20back.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20on%20all%20sides%20of%20the%20layoff%20nightmare%3A%20I've%20been%20a%20victim%20myself%2C%20the%20manager%20in%20the%20room%2C%20and%20the%20executive%20responsible.%20In%20my%20over%2040%20years%20in%20business%2C%20including%20being%20the%20VP%20of%20HR%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20I've%20seen%20too%20many%20layoffs%20for%20one%20lifetime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%20I'm%20an%20advisor%20to%20executives%20and%20others%20who%20face%20layoffs%2C%20from%20both%20sides.%20Part%20of%20my%20work%20is%20to%20help%20the%20people%20affected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20way%20I've%20helped%20is%20with%20a%20comprehensive%20guide%20to%20doing%20layoffs%20well.%20It's%20everything%20I've%20learned%20about%20how%20a%20company%20can%20make%20a%20layoff%20work%20for%20everyone%20involved%2C%20as%20much%20as%20it%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I'll%20be%20honest%2C%20most%20companies%20don't%20do%20that.%20They%20handle%20layoffs%20badly.%20In%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20even%20the%20last%20few%20weeks%2C%20we've%20seen%20a%20parade%20of%20companies%20handle%20layoffs%20with%20process%20and%20timing%20that%20verges%20on%20cruelty.%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspotify-wrapped-2023-layoffs-before-christmas-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI'm%20looking%20at%20you%2C%20Spotify.%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20help%20you%20survive%20this%2C%20here's%20what%20I%20would%20do%20if%20I%20was%20laid%20off.%20Note%20that%20I'm%20not%20a%20lawyer.%20Some%20of%20the%20below%20may%20not%20apply%20or%20even%20be%20legal%20where%20you%20are.%20Take%20this%20all%20as%20my%20thoughts%20and%20opinion%2C%20not%20legal%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Read%20carefully%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20and%20most%20important%20thing%20to%20do%20is%20breathe%2C%20or%20at%20least%20not%20act%20rashly.%20You'll%20be%20told%20you're%20laid%20off%2C%20and%20almost%20instantly%2C%20there%20will%20be%20a%20flurry%20of%20paperwork%20shoved%20at%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20in%20the%20company's%20interest%20to%20get%20this%20over%20instantly%20and%20get%20you%20out%2C%20get%20your%20file%20closed%2C%20and%20move%20on.%20That%20saves%20them%20time%2C%20money%2C%20and%20drama.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey'll%20offer%20you%20a%20tidy%20package%20with%20pages%20and%20pages%20of%20stuff.%20Then%20ask%20%E2%80%94%20even%20demand%20%E2%80%94%20that%20you%20sign%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDon't.%20Not%20right%20away.%20Say%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20need%20time%20to%20understand%20this%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20should%20take%20it%20home%20and%20read%20the%20information%20comprehensively%2C%20every%20single%20word.%20Some%20of%20it%20will%20be%20legalese%2C%20some%20will%20be%20intentionally%20complicated%2C%20some%20will%20be%20optional%20but%20not%20say%20so%20clearly.%20All%20of%20it%20will%20be%20important%20and%20binding%2C%20so%20understand%20it%20before%20you%20sign%20anything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Consider%20pushing%20back%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20should%20consider%2C%20at%20least%20for%20a%20moment%2C%20if%20you%20have%20any%20leverage%20in%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeverage%20can%20come%20in%20many%20forms.%20Perhaps%20you're%20in%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eeoc.gov%2Femployers%2Fsmall-business%2F3-who-protected-employment-discrimination%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20protected%20class%20(age%2C%20gender%2C%20and%20so%20on).%3C%2Fa%3E%20Perhaps%20you%20have%20a%20condition%20that%20changes%20your%20status%20(you're%20pregnant%2C%20on%20medical%20leave%2C%20etc.).%20Perhaps%20you%20have%20extended%20tenure%20or%20specialized%20knowledge%20the%20company%20is%20dependent%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20leverage%20may%20allow%20you%20to%20push%20back%20on%20the%20package%20you've%20been%20offered.%20It%20rarely%20reverses%20the%20layoff%20decision%2C%20but%20it%20might%20change%20the%20terms.%20You%20might%20press%20for%20a%20larger%20severance%2C%20longer%20benefits%2C%20or%20some%20other%20modification%20to%20the%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20part%20of%20a%20large%20layoff%20(more%20than%20a%20dozen%20or%20so)%2C%20your%20leverage%20is%20diluted%20substantially.%20If%20it's%20a%20major%20layoff%20(hundreds)%20your%20leverage%20is%20very%20limited.%20The%20company%20will%20have%20invested%20huge%20amounts%20of%20HR%20and%20legal%20time%20making%20sure%20the%20package%20is%20correct%20and%20legal.%20They%20will%20have%20little%20stomach%20for%20any%20changes%20for%20an%20individual.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20my%20opinion%2C%20you%20should%20almost%20always%20try.%20You%20don't%20get%20what%20you%20don't%20ask%20for.%20So%20pushing%20back%20by%20asking%20for%20a%20larger%20severance%2C%20perhaps%20longer%20health%20care%20coverage%2C%20or%20even%20a%20later%20termination%20date%20is%20worth%20a%20shot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMake%20the%20case%20not%20on%20sympathy%2C%20but%20on%20business%20terms%3A%20You%20need%20time%20to%20organize%20and%20document%20your%20work%20for%20the%20successor%2C%20you're%20in%20a%20specialized%20field%20where%20it%20will%20take%20longer%20to%20find%20another%20job%2C%20you%20have%20a%20medical%20need%20pending%20that%20requires%20coverage%20throughout%20%E2%80%94%20some%20case%20that%20speaks%20business%20and%20money%2C%20not%20heartstrings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20worst%20they%20can%20say%20is%20no.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Consider%20legal%20options%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%2C%20however%2C%20you%20are%20in%20a%20protected%20class%2C%20or%20have%20some%20other%20special%20status%2C%20you%20should%20consider%20getting%20legal%20advice%20or%20even%20have%20a%20lawyer%20just%20review%20the%20paperwork.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recommend%20working%20with%20a%20lawyer%20who%20works%20on%20contingency.%20They%20charge%20nothing%20up%20front%20but%20take%20their%20fees%20from%20any%20resulting%20settlement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20advantage%20is%20clear%20from%20an%20economic%20perspective.%20You%20don't%20have%20to%20find%20a%20substantial%20fee%2C%20at%20a%20time%20when%20you%20just%20lost%20your%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20real%20advantage%20is%20you%20can%20test%20your%20case.%20A%20lawyer%20who%20works%20on%20contingency%20will%20not%20take%20a%20case%20they%20don't%20have%20a%20solid%20chance%20to%20win.%20If%20they%20won't%20take%20your%20case%2C%20it's%20a%20stiff%20uphill%20battle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20strongly%20recommend%20against%20self-funding%20your%20case.%20This%20often%20happens%20out%20of%20anger%20or%20a%20desire%20for%20revenge.%20You're%20mad%2C%20and%20a%20lawyer%20won't%20take%20it%20%E2%80%94%20I%20understand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20you're%20facing%20a%20company%20with%20substantial%20resources.%20You're%20also%20now%20out%20of%20work.%20Unless%20you%20face%20the%20potential%20for%20huge%20upside%2C%20with%20punitive%20damages%20well%20beyond%20simple%20restitution%2C%20you're%20unlikely%20to%20come%20out%20ahead%20financially.%20And%2C%20if%20there%20was%20such%20an%20upside%2C%20a%20contingency%20attorney%20would%20take%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20talk%20to%20a%20lawyer%20if%20you're%20even%20thinking%20about%20it.%20Here%20too%2C%20the%20worst%20they%20can%20say%20is%20%26quot%3Bno.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20Tune%20up%20your%20%3Cstrong%3Er%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20and%20LinkedIn%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOK%2C%20it's%20over%2C%20you're%20done.%20It's%20time%20to%20look%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20haven't%20already%20done%20it%2C%20you%20need%20to%20really%20tune%20up%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20and%20LinkedIn%20profile.%20It%20should%20have%20your%20latest%20work%2C%20position%20and%20titles%2C%20and%20big%20accomplishments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeeping%20these%20up%20to%20date%20on%20a%20running%20basis%20is%20best%2C%20to%20be%20sure.%20But%20if%20you%20haven't%2C%20now%20you%20need%20to%20really%20get%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20find%20more%20information%20and%20opinions%20on%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20and%20LinkedIn%20profiles%20on%20social%20media%20than%20you%20could%20ever%20use.%20Certainly%20review%20what%20they%20say%2C%20listen%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20various%20perspectives.%20But%20do%20what%20feels%20right%20for%20you%20and%20your%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDon't%20pay%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20guru%20or%20LinkedIn%20wizard%20to%20help%20you.%20There%20are%20enough%20people%20offering%20great%20advice%20for%20free.%20Don't%20spend%20hundreds%20of%20your%20precious%20dollars%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20desperate%20you%20feel.%20Their%20advice%20will%20be%20from%20their%20well-worn%20playbook%20and%20probably%20won't%20represent%20you%20as%20well%20as%20you%20can%20represent%20yourself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E5.%20Go%20modest%20when%20taking%20it%20public%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20thing%20to%20consider%2C%20after%20your%20profile%20is%20perfected%2C%20is%20should%20you%20go%20public%20about%20your%20situation%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20three%20typical%20choices%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStealth%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThis%20option%20is%20to%20simply%20change%20the%20end%20date%20on%20your%20current%20job%20on%20LinkedIn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EModest%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThis%20option%20is%20to%20do%20the%20stealth%20option%20above%20and%20also%20include%20a%20small%20LinkedIn%20post.%20I%20recommend%20at%20most%20a%20couple%20of%20sentences.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20sorry%20to%20say%20I%20was%20affected%20by%20the%20recent%20layoff%20at%20XX.%20I%20enjoyed%20my%20time%20there%20and%20look%20forward%20to%20my%20next%20adventure.%26quot%3B%20Or%20something%20similar.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EGood%20friends%20and%20contacts%20will%20reach%20out%20to%20you%2C%20which%20is%20exactly%20what%20you%20want%2C%20but%20you%20aren't%20making%20a%20scene.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWide%20open%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThis%20final%20option%20is%20the%20extended%20post.%20These%20often%20have%20details%20of%20the%20events%20leading%20up%20to%20it%2C%20lots%20of%20gory%20details%2C%20and%20frankly%20TMI.%20These%20posts%20frequently%20are%20filled%20with%20vitriol%20for%20the%20company%2C%20and%20lots%20of%20appeals%20to%20sympathy.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EI%20strongly%20recommend%20against%20this%20kind%20of%20post.%20You're%20burning%20the%20bridges%20behind%20you.%20People%20you%20might%20use%20as%20connections%20or%20references%20will%20get%20damaged%20by%20the%20shrapnel.%20Worse%2C%20you're%20telling%20any%20potential%20future%20employers%20that%20you're%20prone%20to%20drama.%20You%20don't%20handle%20adversity%20well%2C%20and%20often%20do%20so%20publicly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20stick%20to%20a%20modest%20post%20and%20save%20the%20drama%20for%20the%20private%20conversations%20with%20friends%20over%20a%20drink.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20been%20a%20recent%20debate%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-open-to-work-tag-red-flag-desperation-recruiter-says-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhether%20you%20should%20have%20the%20%26quot%3Bopen%20to%20work%26quot%3B%20flag%20set%20on%20your%20LinkedIn%20profile%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20to%20worry%20about%20when%20you're%20out%20of%20work%3B%20this%20is%20probably%20not%20one%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20it%20were%20me%2C%20I'd%20first%20try%20to%20connect%20with%20my%20network.%20Try%20to%20find%20a%20job%20through%20people%20I%20know.%20And%20if%20that%20fails%2C%20go%20for%20more%20broadscale%20approaches%2C%20such%20as%20looking%20at%20job%20sites%2C%20and%20changing%20my%20profile%20on%20LinkedIn%20to%20indicate%20I'm%20looking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E6.%20Work%20your%20network%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20important%20forward-looking%20advice%20is%20to%20dig%20deep%20into%20your%20network.%20Connect%20with%20everyone%20you%20know%20who%20might%20have%20knowledge%20of%20an%20open%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20very%20best%20hires%20are%20made%20through%20connections.%20From%20both%20sides%2C%20a%20job%20placement%20made%20via%20a%20personal%20connection%20is%20the%20best.%20The%20hiring%20company%20has%20the%20advantage%20of%20knowing%20you're%20a%20credible%20person.%20You%20have%20the%20advantage%20of%20knowing%20someone%20who%20works%20there.%20It's%20a%20win-win.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConnect%20with%20lots%20of%20people%2C%20tens%20of%20them%2C%20all%20preferably%20one%20on%20one.%20Maybe%20for%20a%20zoom%20or%20a%20coffee.%20Check%20up%20on%20them%2C%20not%20on%20you.%20Of%20course%2C%20they%20know%20you're%20only%20reaching%20out%20because%20you're%20out%20of%20work.%20That%20doesn't%20mean%20you%20have%20to%20make%20it%20all%20about%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsk%20them%20what%20they%20are%20doing.%20What%20is%20interesting%2C%20what%20is%20hard%2C%20what%20makes%20them%20happy%20where%20they%20work%3F%20Ask%20great%20questions%20about%20their%20job%20and%20life%2C%20and%20get%20them%20to%20think%20you're%20a%20thoughtful%2C%20smart%20person%20who%20they'd%20like%20to%20work%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20spring%20it%20on%20them%3A%20%26quot%3BHey%20as%20you%20know%2C%20I'm%20recently%20out%20of%20work%2C%20I%20was%20wondering%20if%20you%20know%20of%20any%20open%20positions.%20Are%20there%20jobs%20at%20your%20company%2C%20or%20is%20there%20anyone%20you%20know%20who%20is%20hiring%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDon't%20make%20it%20a%20big%20deal%2C%20and%20not%20the%20whole%20point%20of%20the%20conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20the%20answer%20is%20no%2C%20not%20now.%20But%20you've%20planted%20a%20great%20seed%20and%20expanded%20your%20network.%20The%20person%20you%20talked%20to%20will%20be%20at%20some%20meeting%20or%20conference%20or%20dinner%20with%20a%20friend%20who%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BWe're%20having%20such%20a%20hard%20time%20finding%20someone%20for%20this%20job.%26quot%3B%20Your%20contact%20will%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20know%E2%80%A6%20I%20know%20someone.%26quot%3B%20And%20off%20you%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20plant%20lots%20of%20seeds%2C%20and%20if%20it's%20taking%20a%20long%20time%2C%20water%20them%20by%20circling%20back%20around%20a%20month%20or%20so%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20great%20network%20is%20what%20will%20get%20you%20through%20being%20laid%20off.%20They'll%20be%20a%20source%20of%20support%20and%20encouragement.%20They'll%20be%20a%20source%20of%20ideas%20and%20more%20connections%2C%20and%20they%20could%20well%20be%20the%20source%20of%20your%20next%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20of%20course%20you%20should%20consider%20applying%20for%20jobs%20from%20people%20you%20don't%20know%2C%20but%20never%20sell%20your%20connections%20short.%20Even%20if%20you're%20not%20laid%20off%2C%20you%20should%20be%20building%20your%20network.%20It's%20your%20most%20important%20career%20asset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.clwill.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EChris%20Williams%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20the%20former%20vice%20president%20of%20HR%20at%20Microsoft%20and%20a%20leadership%20advisor%2C%20podcaster%2C%20TikTok%20creator%2C%20and%20author.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-do-after-layoff-former-vp-hr-at-microsoft-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701944761000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6570fd640ec98e92f74cfa77%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-do-after-layoff-former-vp-hr-at-microsoft-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22You%20can%20follow%20these%20steps%20after%20being%20laid%20off%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20to%20do%20next.%20Chris%20Williams%2C%20the%20former%20VP%20of%20HR%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20writes%20don't%20sign%20your%20package%20right%20away.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Chris%20Williams%20)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3