0IU%20is%20currently%20in%20the%20final%20stages%20of%20filming%20her%20project%20'You%20Have%20Done%20Well'%3B%20IU%20and%20V%20had%20already%20shot%20their%20collaborative%20music%20video%20before%20V's%20enlistment%3B%20IU's%20highly%20anticipated%20new%20album%20is%20set%20to%20release%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20upcoming%20year%3B%20This%20collaboration%20reunites%20IU%20and%20director%20Um%20Tae%20Hwa%2C%20who%20previously%20worked%20together%20for%20IU's%2010th-anniversary%20concert.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fk-pop%2Fmusic%2Fnews%2Fiu-and-vs-collaboration-music-video-is-helmed-by-concrete-utopia-director%2Farticleshow%2F105811403.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20next%20lucrative%20side%20hustle%3A%20selling%20electricity%20to%20your%20neighbors%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Solar%20power%20turning%20into%20cash%20flow.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6566209dfe5bc6545ebcf7cc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EInstead%20of%20relying%20on%20monolithic%20utilities%20to%20keep%20the%20lights%20on%2C%20the%20rising%20popularity%20of%20solar%20panels%20and%20battery%20storage%20could%20allow%20average%20Americans%20to%20sell%20electricity%20to%20their%20neighbors.%3Cp%3ENolan%20Pelletier%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%2C%20electricity%20has%20flowed%20one%20way%3A%20from%20power%20producers%20to%20public%20utilities%2C%20which%20then%20distribute%20it%20over%20vast%20distances%20to%20households%20and%20businesses.%20That%20utility-to-consumer%20status%20quo%2C%20however%2C%20is%20getting%20challenged.%20A%20growing%20number%20of%20Americans%20have%20started%20generating%20electricity%20from%20solar%20panels%20installed%20at%20their%20homes.%20And%20new%20technologies%20and%20a%20fleet%20of%20startups%20are%20allowing%20people%20to%20not%20only%20independently%20power%20their%20homes%20but%20also%20store%20and%20sell%20excess%20solar%20power%20to%20their%20neighbors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20this%20shift%2C%20small-scale%20energy%20generation%20and%20storage%20facilities%20(like%20a%20residential%20building%20outfitted%20with%20a%20solar%20panel%20and%20battery)%20could%20not%20only%20become%20a%20source%20of%20income%20for%20the%20people%20who%20own%20the%20tech%20but%20it%20could%20improve%20things%20for%20everyone%20else.%20People%20on%20the%20traditional%20grid%20could%20see%20lower%20costs%2C%20greater%20grid%20reliability%2C%20and%20less%20volatile%20energy%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20relying%20on%20monolithic%20utilities%20and%20power%20plants%20to%20keep%20the%20lights%20on%2C%20the%20rising%20popularity%20of%20solar%20panels%20and%20battery%20storage%20might%20upend%20the%20unidirectional%20utility%20power%20model%20and%20electricity%20markets.%20The%20country's%20electrical%20grid%20is%20quickly%20turning%20from%20a%20river%20into%20a%20lake%2C%20with%20people%20able%20to%20generate%2C%20share%2C%20and%20make%20money%20off%20their%20own%20electricity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPower%20plants%20on%20every%20roof%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20home-installed%20solar%20industry%20is%20still%20a%20small%20slice%20of%20the%20country's%20energy%20generation%2C%20the%20number%20of%20people%20putting%20panels%20on%20their%20roofs%20is%20growing%20rapidly.%20Six%20percent%20of%20single-family%2C%20owner-occupied%20homes%20in%20the%20US%20had%20rooftop%20solar%20panels%20at%20the%20end%20of%202022%2C%20generating%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.seia.org%2Fresearch-resources%2Fsolar-market-insight-report-2022-year-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20about%2037%20million%20megawatt%20hours%20a%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20enough%20to%20power%203%20million%20to%204%20million%20households.%20And%20the%20rate%20of%20residential%20installation%20is%20booming%3A%20A%20record%20700%2C000%20homeowners%20installed%20arrays%20in%202022%2C%20according%20to%20the%20trade%20group%20Solar%20Energy%20Industries%20Association.%20Though%20the%20overall%20percentage%20of%20Americans%20with%20rooftop%20solar%20remains%20low%2C%20some%20states%20are%20much%20further%20down%20the%20road%3A%20California%2C%20Texas%2C%20and%20Florida%20were%20the%20top%20three%20in%20solar-installation%20capacity%20for%20the%20past%20three%20years.%20Many%20more%20people%20will%20be%20incentivized%20to%20install%20solar%20power%20and%20energy%20storage%20with%20the%20subsidies%20provided%20by%20the%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energy.gov%2Feere%2Fsolar%2Fhomeowners-guide-federal-tax-credit-solar-photovoltaics%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESolar%20Investment%20Tax%20Credit%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20addition%20to%20taking%20power%20production%20into%20their%20own%20hands%2C%20many%20of%20these%20households%20are%20also%20installing%20battery-storage%20units%2C%20which%20collect%20surplus%20energy%20to%20be%20used%20on%20a%20(literal)%20rainy%20day%20or%20sold%20back%20into%20the%20grid.%20Beyond%20home%20setups%2C%20community%20solar%20%E2%80%94%20a%20system%20in%20which%20customers%20can%20subscribe%20to%20power%20produced%20by%20a%20local%20solar%20project%20%E2%80%94%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.review-energy.com%2Fsolar%2Fcumulative-us-community-solar-capacity-will-reach-nearly-14-gw-by-2028%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThus%252C%2520community%2520solar%2520growth%2520is%2Ccumulative%2520capacity%2520expected%2520by%25202028.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpected%20to%20grow%20by%208%25%20%3C%2Fa%3Ea%20year%20through%202028%2C%20eventually%20generating%2014%20gigawatts%2C%20enough%20to%20power%20over%2010%20million%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20a%20household%20generates%20its%20own%20power%20and%20has%20a%20battery%20that%20stores%20excess%20energy%2C%20there%20are%20a%20few%20ways%20a%20homeowner%20could%20earn%20income%20from%20the%20tech.%20One%20way%20is%20to%20simply%20sell%20excess%20supply%20back%20to%20their%20utility%2C%20which%20pays%20the%20customer%20a%20fee%20for%20the%20right%20to%20distribute%20the%20electricity%20elsewhere.%20One%20of%20the%20largest%20California%20utilities%2C%20PG%26amp%3BE%2C%20partnered%20with%20the%20solar-energy%20startup%20Sunrun%20to%20pilot%20such%20a%20program%2C%20which%20paid%20customers%20an%20up-front%20%24750%20fee%20for%20the%20right%20to%20sell%20their%20stored%20energy%20to%20other%20customers%20on%20hot%20summer%20nights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20market%20may%20become%20more%20lucrative%20for%20homeowners.%20Many%20newer%20solar%20setups%20use%20smart%20technology%2C%20which%20could%20determine%20the%20optimal%20energy-selling%20strategy.%20When%20spot%20energy%20prices%20are%20cheap%2C%20out-of-the-box%20trading%20software%20could%20buy%20power%20from%20the%20grid%20to%20power%20the%20household%20and%20store%20the%20solar%20energy%20generated%20on%20the%20roof.%20When%20prices%20are%20higher%2C%20it%20could%20sell%20excess%20supply%20from%20the%20battery%20back%20to%20a%20utility%2C%20thus%20maximizing%20the%20payments.%20Arcadia%2C%20a%20Washington%2C%20DC-based%20startup%20launched%20in%202014%2C%20already%20collects%20meter%20data%20from%20utilities%20to%20help%20its%20customers%20track%20carbon%20exposure%20and%20predict%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2022-12-16%2Farcadia-wants-to-bring-venmo-like-ease-to-managing-electricity-use%3FleadSource%3Duverify%2520wall%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoptimal%20times%20in%20the%20day%20to%20purchase%20electricity%20on%20the%20open%20market%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20algorithmic%20trading%20program%20could%20help%20homeowners%20turn%20a%20passive%20profit%20and%20help%20smooth%20demand%20on%20the%20broader%20grid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20greater%20autonomy%20in%20power%20production%20and%20consumption%20may%20allow%20people%20to%20use%20the%20electrical%20devices%20they%20buy%20as%20mini%20batteries%20%E2%80%94%20a%20refrigerator%20or%20an%20electric%20vehicle%20might%20dynamically%20interact%20with%20the%20electricity%20market%20to%20charge%20themselves%20when%20power%20prices%20are%20low%20and%20feed%20some%20of%20their%20energy%20back%20to%20other%20devices%20when%20prices%20are%20higher.%20The%20US%20Department%20of%20Energy%20even%20gave%20a%20name%20to%20these%20aggregations%20of%20distributed%20resources%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energy.gov%2Flpo%2Farticles%2Fintroducing-vppieces-bite-sized-blogs-about-virtual-power-plants%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evirtual%20power%20plants%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20DOE's%20report%20on%20the%20future%20of%20VPPs%20projects%20that%20the%20tech%20could%20eventually%20generate%2080%20to%20160%20gigawatts%20of%20power%20annually%2C%20which%20could%20supply%20up%20to%2020%25%20of%20energy%20needs%20during%20times%20of%20peak%20demand%20in%202030%20%E2%80%94%20while%20costing%2040%25%20to%2060%25%20less%20than%20alternatives%20such%20as%20natural%20gas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225150%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20a%20young%20family%20in%20front%20of%20a%20home%20with%20solar%20panels%20on%20the%20roof.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F649993cc65b9ce0018a4bc77%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223672%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlgorithmic%20trading%20program%20could%20help%20homeowners%20sell%20some%20of%20their%20energy%20back%20into%20the%20grid%2C%20earning%20them%20a%20passive%20profit.%3Cp%3EHenglein%20and%20Steets%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20option%20for%20homeowners%20is%20peer-to-peer%20energy%20trading.%20Instead%20of%20selling%20the%20electricity%20to%20the%20utility%2C%20which%20then%20distributes%20it%2C%20people%20could%20agree%20to%20sell%20their%20excess%20power%20directly%20to%20their%20neighbors%20using%20pre-existing%20grid%20infrastructure.%20While%20this%20sort%20of%20energy%20sharing%20would%20still%20require%20the%20physical%20cables%2C%20substations%2C%20or%20other%20infrastructure%20owned%20by%20a%20utility%20or%20a%20city%20(for%20which%20they%20would%20charge%20some%20fee)%2C%20people%20could%20use%20third-party%20apps%20to%20buy%20and%20sell%20electricity%20directly%20from%20homes%20and%20businesses%20in%20their%20community%20that%20are%20using%20solar%20panels.%20Australia's%20Localvolts%2C%20for%20example%2C%20allows%20consumers%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flocalvolts.com%2Fbulletins%2Fpeer-to-peer-electricity%2Fpeople-trading-electricity-among-themselves%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enegotiate%20peer-to-peer%20clean-power%20contracts%3C%2Fa%3E%20using%20an%20online-trading%20platform%20%E2%80%94%20similar%20to%20buying%20stocks%20from%20an%20online%20broker.%20Users%20buy%20and%20sell%20electricity%20with%20any%20counterparty%2C%20whether%20it's%20a%20neighbor%20or%20the%20broader%20electricity%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20kind%20of%20energy%20trading%20could%20eventually%20scale%20up%20so%20that%20consumers%20could%20customize%20their%20energy%20use%20depending%20on%20their%20needs%20and%20particular%20preferences.%20For%20instance%2C%20someone%20may%20elect%20to%20only%20buy%20clean%20energy%20produced%20by%20a%20specific%20group%20(small%20local%20businesses%2C%20for%20instance)%20or%20from%20a%20select%20set%20of%20producers%20based%20on%20various%20environmental%2C%20social%2C%20or%20geographical%20characteristics.%20While%20the%20central%20electrical%20utility%20would%20still%20be%20needed%20as%20a%20backup%20as%20the%20market%20scales%2C%20with%20enough%20surplus%2C%20the%20big%20players%20might%20eventually%20be%20cut%20out%20of%20supplying%20power%20to%20some%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20win-win%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDistributed%20energy%20and%20virtual%20power%20plants%20are%20obviously%20beneficial%20to%20the%20people%20who%20decide%20to%20sell%20off%20their%20electricity%20%E2%80%94%20customers%20with%20installed%20solar%20roof%20capacity%20already%20save%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.next10.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2021-02%2FNext10-electricity-rates-v2.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24200%20in%20yearly%20energy%20expenditures%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20they%20could%20save%20%24500%20or%20more%20each%20year%20with%20the%20technological%20improvements%20provided%20by%20peer-to-peer%20energy%20trading%20and%20smart%20appliances.%20Beyond%20becoming%20a%20side%20hustle%20for%20sun-drenched%20homeowners%2C%20the%20new%20technology%20also%20has%20plenty%20of%20benefits%20for%20non-income%20generators%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeer-to-peer%20energy%20sharing%20could%20drive%20down%20the%20cost%20of%20power%20for%20all%20consumers.%20The%20relatively%20cheap%20cost%20to%20produce%20solar%20electricity%20and%20the%20shorter%20distances%20to%20transport%20the%20power%20make%20it%20a%20more%20cost-effective%20option%20for%20those%20who%20are%20able%20to%20access%20VPPs%20and%20other%20energy-saving%20devices.%20There%20are%2C%20of%20course%2C%20concerns%20about%20the%20reliability%20of%20solar%20energy.%20While%20energy%20decentralization%20can't%20solve%20all%20of%20those%20problems%20%E2%80%94%20if%20the%20sun%20doesn't%20shine%20for%20a%20week%2C%20then%20consumers%20will%20have%20to%20rely%20on%20backup%20energy%20from%20the%20main%20grid%20%E2%80%94%20a%20network%20of%20distributed%20energy%20suppliers%20and%20storage%20backup%20can%20ease%20the%20peak%20loads%20so%20that%20utilities%20are%20able%20to%20better%20deploy%20their%20own%20energy.%20In%20a%20world%20with%20more%20self-sustaining%20households%2C%20the%20grid%20becomes%20more%20reliable%20and%20less%20prone%20to%20blackouts%20while%20consumers%20become%20less%20vulnerable%20to%20one-off%20price%20shocks%20during%20sudden%20heat%20spikes%20or%20deep%20freezes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20evidence%20shows%20that%20the%20savings%20and%20increased%20reliability%20could%20be%20widespread.%20The%20purchase%20and%20installation%20of%20a%20distributed%20energy%20resource%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Femp.lbl.gov%2Fpublications%2Fincome-trends-among-us-residential%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eappears%20equitable%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20income%20ranges.%20In%20fact%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Femp.lbl.gov%2Fsolar-demographics-tool%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehouseholds%20with%20incomes%20under%20%24100%2C000%20made%20up%20half%20of%20solar%20adoption%20in%202021%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20growth%20of%20peer-to-peer%20power%20plants%20would%20also%20be%20a%20boost%20for%20the%20government's%20investment%20in%20green%20energy.%20The%20return%20on%20investment%20afforded%20by%20bill%20savings%20and%20surplus%20power%20sales%20would%20also%20reduce%20the%20need%20for%20government%20subsidies%20and%20tax%20breaks%20on%20clean%20power%20and%20storage%2C%20a%20benefit%20for%20fiscal%20planning%20and%20governmental%20budgeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMaking%20it%20a%20reality%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAustralia%2C%20much%20of%20the%20EU%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20and%2014%20US%20states%20allow%20electricity%20customers%20to%20choose%20their%20own%20power%20retailers.%20Texas%20and%20California%2C%20two%20of%20the%20largest%20solar-generating%20states%20in%20the%20US%2C%20have%20deregulated%20the%20electricity%20trade%20and%20allow%20the%20free%20flow%20of%20power%2C%20and%20more%20states%20may%20follow%20in%20their%20footsteps%20once%20the%20benefits%20of%20VPPs%20and%20DERs%20materialize.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20more%20consumers%20join%20local%20power%20networks%20through%20platforms%20like%20Arcadia%20and%20Localvolts%2C%20the%20virtuous%20cycle%20of%20market%20forces%20and%20price%20competition%20could%20lower%20electricity%20prices.%20The%20optimization%20of%20power%20consumption%20may%20also%20lead%20to%20an%20imaginative%20reassessment%20of%20home%20devices%20and%20vehicles%3A%20Instead%20of%20blindly%20consuming%20energy%20while%20they%20charge%2C%20gadgets%20attached%20to%20the%20grid%20could%20become%20sources%20of%20energy%20in%20a%20shortage.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20charging%20an%20electric%20car%20will%20come%20down%20as%20the%20vehicle%20learns%20to%20grab%20power%20from%20the%20grid%20only%20when%20prices%20are%20cheap%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20could%20even%20become%20a%20battery%20for%20other%20appliances%20in%20a%20pinch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20world%20grapples%20with%20the%20need%20to%20shift%20away%20from%20oil%20and%20other%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20people%20will%20be%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20make%20the%20electrical%20transition%20more%20cost-effective%20and%20secure.%20By%20connecting%20solar-powered%20homes%20to%20neighboring%20houses%20and%20businesses%2C%20people%20could%20make%20some%20money%20while%20providing%20benefits%20for%20other%20consumers%2C%20their%20communities%2C%20and%20the%20planet%20at%20large.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fkartik-menon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EKartik%20Menon%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20former%20Goldman%20Sachs%20securities%20trader%20who%20wrote%20quantitative%20strategies%20to%20trade%20equities%20and%20US-listed%20derivatives.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-passive-income-side-hustle-selling-electricity-neighbors-solar-panels-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701944521000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656620d7fe5bc6545ebcf7f2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-passive-income-side-hustle-selling-el