3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENatalie%20Carroll%20is%20a%20dietitian%20who%20helps%20people%20with%20gynecological%20conditions%20such%20as%20PCOS.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20her%20own%20life%2C%20she%20takes%20three%20daily%20supplements%20that%20can%20help%20with%20energy%20and%20inflammation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20takes%20a%20multivitamin%2C%20vitamin%20D%2C%20and%20omega-3%20fatty%20acids.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENatalie%20Carroll%20has%20dedicated%20her%20career%20to%20helping%20women%20with%20gynecological%20conditions%20such%20as%20PCOS%20and%20endometriosis%2C%20pregnant%20people%2C%20and%20those%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fobgyn-shannon-clark-on-useless-prenatal-vitamins-fertility-supplements-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efertility%20struggles%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarroll%2C%20who%20is%20a%20registered%20dietitian-nutritionist%20based%20in%20New%20York%20and%20works%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.topnutritioncoaching.com%2Fnutritionists-near-me%2Ffort-worth%23natalie-carroll%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETop%20Nutrition%20Coaching%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20believes%20in%20a%20food-first%20approach%20to%20addressing%20nutrient%20gaps%20in%20a%20person's%20diet%20and%20symptom%20management.%20But%20said%20that%20in%20certain%20situations%2C%20supplements%20can%20%26quot%3Bbridge%20the%20gap%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20get%20us%20%26quot%3Bwhere%20we%20need%20to%20be%20in%20our%20health.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20recommending%20supplements%2C%20however%2C%20she%20assesses%20her%20client's%20diet%20and%20ensures%20that%20they%20understand%20what%20the%20supplement%20will%20do%20for%20them%2C%20and%20how%20to%20get%20it%20from%20a%20reputable%20source.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarroll%20shared%20the%20three%20supplements%20that%20she%20takes%20in%20her%20own%20life%20that%20help%20her%20keep%20on%20top%20of%20all%20the%20nutrients%20she%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20high-quality%20multivitamin%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECaroll%20takes%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fmultivitamins-for-memory-older-adults-benefit-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehigh-quality%20multivitamin%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20daily%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20her%20nutrient%20needs%20are%20met.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20started%20taking%20it%20about%20a%20year%20before%20she%20got%20pregnant%20with%20her%20first%20child%2C%20she%20said%2C%20and%20chose%20one%20that%20contained%20folic%20acid%2C%20a%20synthetic%20version%20of%20the%20naturally%20occurring%20form%20of%20vitamin%20B9.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fncbddd%2Ffolicacid%2Fabout.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DWhy%2520folic%2520acid%2520is%2520important%2Cand%2520spine%2520(spina%2520bifida).%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECenters%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20every%20woman%20of%20reproductive%20age%20should%20take%20400%20micrograms%20of%20folic%20acid%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20because%20half%20of%20pregnancies%20are%20unplanned%2C%20and%20when%20a%20baby%20is%20developing%20in%20early%20pregnancy%2C%20folic%20acid%20helps%20form%20the%20neural%20tube%2C%20which%20goes%20on%20to%20become%20the%20brain%20and%20spine.%20Folic%20acid%20can%20help%20prevent%20some%20major%20brain%20and%20spine%20birth%20defects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarroll%20said%20that%20if%20you%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fcardiologist-takes-supplements-folic-acid-b12-vitamin-d-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrying%20to%20get%20pregnant%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20should%20also%20make%20sure%20your%20multivitamin%20contains%20choline%2C%20a%20nutrient%20found%20in%20beef%2C%20chicken%20liver%2C%20and%20eggs.%20Experts%20recommend%20getting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.acog.org%2Fwomens-health%2Ffaqs%2Fnutrition-during-pregnancy%23%3A~%3Atext%3DExperts%2520recommend%2520that%2520you%2520get%2Cneeds%2520while%2520you%2520are%2520pregnant.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E450%20milligrams%20of%20choline%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20each%20day%20during%20pregnancy%20to%20aid%20fetal%20brain%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EVitamin%20D%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECarroll%20lives%20in%20an%20area%20that%20doesn't%20get%20a%20lot%20of%20sun%2C%20she%20said%2C%20and%20has%20been%20deficient%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fvitamin-d-and-longevity-anti-aging-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Evitamin%20D%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Fvitamin-d-deficiency%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESymptoms%20of%20vitamin%20D%20deficiency%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20include%20fatigue%2C%20bone%20pain%2C%20muscle%20weakness%2C%20aches%20or%20cramps%2C%20and%20mood%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20some%20foods%20contain%20vitamin%20D%2C%20which%20is%20crucial%20for%20bone%20and%20teeth%20health%2C%20sunlight%20is%20the%20best%20source.%20But%20it%20can%20be%20tricky%20for%20many%20people%20who%20live%20in%20colder%20climates%20to%20get%20enough%20sunlight%20in%20the%20winter%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20boost%20her%20vitamin%20D%20levels%2C%20Carroll%20takes%20a%20daily%20supplement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EOmega-3%20fatty%20acids%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECarroll%20also%20takes%20omega-3%20fatty%20acids%20for%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Fanti-inflammatory-diet%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eanti-inflammatory%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20heart-protective%20qualities%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20recommend%20having%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Floma-linda-blue-zone-lifestyle-habits-heart-health-inflammation-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etwo%20servings%20of%20fish%20each%20week%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20like%20salmon%2C%20tuna%2C%20or%20sardines%20%E2%80%94%20for%20their%20beneficial%20omega-3%20fatty%20acids%2C%20EPA%2C%20and%20DHA.%20But%20supplements%20can%20be%20a%20good%20source%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20previously%20reported%20that%20a%202022%20study%20found%20getting%20just%203%20grams%20of%20omega-3%20fatty%20acids%20a%20day%20could%20prevent%20heart%20disease%20and%20lower%20blood%20pressure.%20A%20review%20of%2013%20studies%20also%20found%20that%20omega-3%20supplements%20helped%20reduce%20some%20symptoms%20of%20depression%20in%20those%20with%20major%20depressive%20disorder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupplements-dietitian-women-health-specialist-regimen-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701944041000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6570a5290ec98e92f74ca412%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupplements-dietitian-women-health-specialist-regimen-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20dietitian%20specializing%20in%20women's%20health%20issues%20like%20PCOS%20believes%20supplements%20can%20sometimes%20be%20beneficial.%20She%20takes%20vitamin%20D%2C%20omega-3%20fatty%20acids%2C%20and%20a%20multivitamin.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kschewitz%40insider.com%20(Kim%20Schewitz)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupplements-dietitian-women-health-specialist-regimen-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Talor%20Swift%20on%20Kardashian-West%20feud%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701943830000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105811189%2Cimgsize-46364.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fmusic%2Fnews%2Fta