%20see%20what%20would%20happen.%20My%20husband%20works%20in%20IT%2C%20and%20I%20worked%20in%20marketing%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20never%20been%20to%20New%20Zealand%2C%20and%20we%20didn't%20know%20anyone%20there%2C%20but%20we%20didn't%20consider%20moving%20anywhere%20else.%20My%20husband%20mentioned%20New%20Zealand%20one%20day%20on%20a%20long%20car%20ride%20home%20from%20Florida%20to%20Wisconsin.%20I%20spent%20hours%20reading%20up%20on%20the%20country%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20see%20anything%20negative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20wanted%20an%20international%20experience%20somewhere%20that%20was%20English-speaking%20and%20had%20great%20weather%2C%20and%20New%20Zealand%20fit%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20moving%20process%20took%20one%20year%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20about%2012%20months%20from%20deciding%20to%20move%20to%20doing%20it.%20We%20started%20by%20submitting%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.immigration.govt.nz%2Fformshelp%2Fsmc-eoi-form%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eexpression%20of%20interest%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20government%2C%20and%20then%20we%20were%20selected%20to%20do%20the%20full%20visa%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20week%2C%20we%20got%20the%20visa%20approval%20and%20my%20husband%20got%20a%20job%20offer.%20Soon%20after%2C%20we%20moved%20to%20the%20capital%2C%20Wellington%2C%20with%20the%20intention%20of%20being%20there%20for%20two%20years%20%E2%80%94%20the%20duration%20of%20the%20visa%20we%20had.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20loved%20it%2C%20but%20we%20stuck%20with%20our%20plan%20and%20moved%20back%20to%20Milwaukee%20in%202016.%20We%20had%20no%20intention%20of%20going%20back%20to%20New%20Zealand%2C%20though%20we%20missed%20it%20and%20were%20sad%20to%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20found%20our%20way%20back%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20my%20husband%20got%20another%20job%20offer%20in%20New%20Zealand.%20We%20decided%20to%20take%20it%2C%20go%20through%20the%20visa%20process%20again%2C%20and%20move%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20hard%20decision.%20We%20were%20all%20resettled%20in%20Milwaukee%2C%20but%20my%20heart%20was%20still%20in%20New%20Zealand.%20Everyone%20in%20the%20family%20was%20OK%20with%20going%2C%20but%20some%20were%20more%20excited%20than%20others.%20It%20was%20good%20for%20my%20children%20to%20be%20going%20somewhere%20that%20was%20at%20least%20familiar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20my%20children%20ranged%20from%202%20to%2011%20when%20we%20first%20moved%2C%20my%20younger%20two%20kids%20had%20only%20ever%20really%20known%20New%20Zealand.%20My%20youngest%20has%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20Kiwi%20accent%20that%20he%20can%20turn%20on%20and%20off.%20We%20don't%20hear%20it%20much%20at%20home%2C%20but%20when%20he's%20in%20the%20car%20with%20his%20friends%2C%20it's%20funny%20to%20hear%20him%20talk%20like%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20things%20are%20more%20expensive%20here%2C%20but%20college%20is%20more%20affordable%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20New%20Zealand%20is%20more%20expensive%20than%20many%20parts%20of%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20it%20just%20comes%20down%20to%20how%20much%20you%20make.%20The%20cost%20of%20food%20is%20high%2C%20but%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-food-prices-inflation-gas-costs-groceries-restaurants-americans-economy-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecost%20of%20food%20is%20high%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20too%2C%20because%20of%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClothes%20and%20electronics%20in%20New%20Zealand%20are%20more%20expensive%2C%20and%20there's%20noticeably%20less%20choice.%20When%20we%20go%20back%20to%20the%20US%2C%20we%20tend%20to%20shop%20a%20lot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20rented%20a%20house%20both%20times%20we%20moved%20here%20because%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehousing%20is%20very%20expensive%2C%20so%20we%20found%20renting%20to%20be%20our%20best%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20daughter%20attends%20the%20University%20of%20Otago.%20The%20first%20year%20was%20free%2C%20though%20it%20cost%20about%20%249%2C000%20for%20her%20to%20live%20on%20campus.%20My%20son%20goes%20to%20college%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Wisconsin%E2%80%93Whitewater.%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20went%20there%2C%20so%20we%20got%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20discount.%20It%20isn't%20an%20expensive%20school%20by%20US%20standards%2C%20but%20it%20costs%20about%20%2420%2C000%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20work-life%20balance%20in%20New%20Zealand%20is%20better%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20pandemic%2C%20I%20started%20creating%20videos%2C%20and%20now%20I%20have%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2F%40Kiwiamericans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EYouTube%20channel%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20business%20where%20I%20help%20Americans%20move%20to%20New%20Zealand.%20I%20collaborate%20with%20companies%20that%20offer%20visa%20advice%2C%20real-estate%20help%2C%20and%20job%20recruitment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20teach%20marketing%20and%20communication%20business%20courses%20full%20time%20to%20college%20students%20at%20Open%20Polytechnic.%20I%20still%20teach%20a%20few%20writing%20courses%20there%20on%20a%20contract%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20mandatory%20to%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-paid-vacation-time-is-different-around-the-world-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efour%20weeks%20off%20a%20year%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20New%20Zealand%2C%20no%20matter%20your%20job%20or%20whether%20it's%20part%20or%20full%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20started%20working%20here%2C%20it%20was%20an%20adjustment.%20My%20coworkers%20took%20breaks%20at%2010%20a.m.%20for%20morning%20tea%20and%20again%20for%20afternoon%20tea.%20Work%20doesn't%20start%20until%209%20a.m.%2C%20and%20I%20remember%20on%20my%20first%20day%20seeing%20people%20coming%20in%20at%201