0that%20of%20other%20cases%20of%20cross-border%20repression%20by%20Washington%E2%80%99s%20perennial%20adversaries%2C%20including%20China%2C%20Russia%20and%20Iran%2C%20at%20Capitol%20Hill%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpening%20the%20hearing%20of%20the%20full%20Senate%20foreign%20relations%20committee%2C%20the%20chair%2C%20Democrat%20senator%20from%20Maryland%20Ben%20Cardin%2C%20said%20it%20took%20%E2%80%9Cincredible%20courage%E2%80%9D%20for%20exiles%2C%20journalists%2C%20civil%20society%20activists%20and%20human%20rights%20defenders%20to%20%E2%80%9Cspeak%20out%20against%20autocrats%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBoth%20friends%20and%20foes%20send%20their%20agents%20across%20the%20border%20to%20hunt%20down%20and%20harass%20critics.%20Even%20here%20on%20US%20soil%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20noted%20in%20first%20few%20minutes%20of%20the%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20seen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fpannun-assassination-plot-india-enquiry-committee-set-up%5C%22%3Edisturbing%20allegations%20against%20an%20Indian%20government%20official%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20involvement%20in%20planning%20to%20assassinate%20a%20US%20citizen%20in%20New%20York%20who%20was%20critical%20of%20the%20Indian%20government.%20This%20follows%20allegations%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20involvement%20in%20the%20killing%20of%20a%20Canadian%20Sikh%20leader%20earlier%20this%20year.%20The%20Modi%20government%20had%20labelled%20both%20critics%20as%20terrorists%2C%E2%80%9D%20stated%20Cardin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20written%20remarks%2C%20he%20proceeded%20to%20criticise%20China%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20other%20autocratic%20governments%20for%20their%20escalating%20efforts%20to%20target%20journalists%20and%20dissidents%20residing%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTransnational%20repression%20is%20not%20new%2C%20but%20modern%20technology%20has%20expanded%20government%E2%80%99s%20reach%20like%20never%20before%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20US%20official%20to%20use%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Ctransnational%20repression%E2%80%9D%20in%20connection%20with%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fblinken-says-india-should-join-canadian-probe-says-us-takes-transnational-repression-seriously%5C%22%3Ewas%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Anthony%20Blinken%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20he%20insisted%20that%20India%20should%20join%20the%20Canadian%20government%E2%80%99s%20probe%20into%20the%20killing%20of%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foreign.senate.gov%2Fpress%2Fdem%2Frelease%2Fchair-cardin-statement-on-doj-announcement-related-to-foiled-assassination-plot-in-new-york%5C%22%3ELast%20week%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Cardin%20had%20reacted%20to%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Justice%E2%80%99s%20indictment%20that%20Indian%20government%20agents%20had%20tried%20to%20kill%20a%20US%20citizen%20and%20announced%20that%20he%20was%20holding%20a%20hearing%20on%20transnational%20repression.%20While%20the%20indictment%20had%20not%20named%20the%20Sikh%20citizen%2C%20he%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20Gurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannun%2C%20general%20counsel%20of%20%E2%80%98Sikhs%20for%20Justice%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%20to%20the%20Democratic%20chair%2C%20Senator%20Jim%20Risch%2C%20ranking%20member%20of%20the%20committee%20and%20a%20Republican%20from%20Idaho%2C%20also%20brought%20up%20India%20at%20the%20outset%20of%20his%20opening%20comments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGovernments%20who%20have%20gotten%20away%20with%20silencing%20dissent%20inside%20their%20own%20country%20are%20now%20trying%20to%20stifle%20free%20speech%20around%20the%20world%2C%20including%20here%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20Just%20last%20week%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%2C%20who%20the%20Chairman%20referred%20to%2C%20unsealed%20an%20indictment%20alleging%20an%20Indian%20government%20official%20engaged%20in%20a%20plot%20to%20assassinate%20a%20US%20citizen%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Pannun%2C%20Nijjar%20and%20the%20Constant%20Need%20to%20find%20the%20'Enemies'%20of%20Modi's%20India%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fpannun-nijjar-and-the-constant-need-to-find-the-enemies-of-modis-india%5C%22%3EPannun%2C%20Nijjar%20and%20the%20Constant%20Need%20to%20find%20the%20%E2%80%98Enemies%E2%80%99%20of%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20noted%20that%20it%20was%20not%20surprising%20that%20China%20is%20%E2%80%9Cleading%20the%20world%20in%20using%20transnational%20repression%20to%20quash%20any%20sign%20of%20dissent%E2%80%9D.%20Risch%20then%20listed%20cases%20of%20government%20agents%20from%20China%2C%20Russia%2C%20Iran%20and%20Turkey%2C%20targeting%20opposition%20members%20and%20journalists%20settled%20in%20other%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20senators%20suggesting%20various%20proposals%20to%20fight%20transnational%20repression%2C%20Cardin%20announced%20his%20intention%20to%20introduce%20the%20International%20Freedom%20Protection%20Act%20soon.%20While%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20delve%20into%20the%20details%20of%20the%20legislation%2C%20he%20emphasised%20its%20focus%20on%20countering%20transnational%20repression%20employed%20by%20%E2%80%9Cautocratic%20and%20illiberal%20states%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECardin%20also%20said%20that%20advocacy%20group%20Sikh%20Coalition%E2%80%99s%20statement%20had%20been%20taken%20on%20the%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20of%20the%20three%20witnesses%20at%20the%20hearing%20had%20been%20targeted%20by%20the%20Russian%20and%20Chinese%20governments%2C%20so%20it%20was%20not%20surprising%20that%20there%20was%20considerable%20time%20spent%20by%20the%20committee%20members%20on%20those%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20India%20continued%20to%20pop%20up%20several%20times%20during%20the%20hearings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20as%20an%20expert%20witness%2C%20Michael%20Abramowitz%2C%20president%20of%20Freedom%20House%2C%20a%20Washington-based%20non-profit%2C%20said%20that%20China%20alone%20accounted%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffreedomhouse.org%2Freport%2Ftransnational-repression%2Fabout-acknowledgements%5C%22%3E30%25%20of%20all%20incidents%20of%20transnational%20repression%3C%2Fa%3E%20recorded%20by%20his%20organisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20he%20hoped%20that%20the%20US%20government%20would%20address%20such%20cases%20even%20when%20involving%20close%20partners%20and%20allies.%20He%20emphasised%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20United%20States%20must%20not%20hesitate%20to%20raise%20this%20issue%20directly%20at%20the%20highest%20levels%20with%20those%20countries%20perpetrating%20transnational%20repression%2C%20even%20when%20those%20perpetrators%20are%20close%20partners%20such%20as%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTransnational%20repression%20is%20a%20violation%20of%20rights%20and%20sovereignty%20and%20breaks%20the%20bond%20of%20trust%20that%20must%20exist%20for%20deep%20co-operation%20between%20nations.%20Whether%20a%20government%20engages%20in%20transnational%20oppression%20should%20be%20a%20factor%2C%20a%20significant%20factor%2C%20determining%20the%20nature%20of%20bilateral%20relations%20and%20the%20closeness%20of%20any%20partnership%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20asserted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbramowitz%20said%20that%20these%20cases%20should%20be%20part%20of%20the%20bilateral%20conversation.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20this%20is%20seen%20to%20be%20swept%20under%20the%20rug%2C%20other%20countries%20will%20not%20take%20it%20seriously.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDemocrat%20Senator%20Tim%20Kaine%20specifically%20focused%20his%20questions%20on%20how%20to%20deal%20with%20allegations%20made%20against%20Indian%20government%2C%20highlighting%20this%20as%20a%20dilemma%20for%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20read%20out%20paragraphs%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fworld%2Findia%2Ffoiled-plot-to-kill-u-s-sikh-is-linked-to-murder-of-canadian-activist-643b1882%5C%22%3Ean%20article%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3EWall%20Street%20Journa%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3El%3C%2Fem%3E%20about%20the%20DOJ%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fusao-sdny%2Fpr%2Fus-attorney-announces-charges-connection-foiled-plot-assassinate-us-citizen-new-york%5C%22%3Eindictment%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20claimed%20that%20a%20drug%20trafficker%2C%20allegedly%20hired%20by%20an%20Indian%20government%20agent%2C%20had%20told%20a%20%E2%80%98hitman%E2%80%99%20that%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20have%20so%20many%20targets%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThat%E2%80%99s%20the%20case%20that%20has%20been%20recently%20brought%20in%20Federal%20Court%20in%20New%20York%20connecting%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fcanada-accuses-indian-government-of-assassinating-sikh-citizen-in-vancouver-expels-senior-diplomat%5C%22%3Emurder%20of%20the%20Sikh%20activist%20in%20the%20suburb%20of%20Toronto%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20it%20is%20highly%2C%20highly%20disturbing%20to%20say%20the%20least.%20And%20that%20quote%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20have%20so%20many%20targets%E2%80%9D%20is%20something%20we%20need%20to%20pay%20very%20serious%20attention%20to%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Kaine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22From%20Nijjar%20to%20Pannun%2C%20Modi%20Government%E2%80%99s%20Recklessness%20is%20Undermining%20National%20Interest%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fnijjar-pannun-modi-foreign-policy-national-interest%5C%22%3EFrom%20Nijjar%20to%20Pannun%2C%20Modi%20Government%E2%80%99s%20Recklessness%20is%20Undermining%20National%20Interest%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Democrat%20senator%20also%20observed%20that%20there%20was%20a%20noted%20difference%20in%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20angry%20reaction%20to%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20allegations%20versus%20the%20US%20indictment.%20India%20had%20reacted%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20negative%20way%E2%80%9D%20and%20asked%20Ottawa%20to%20withdraw%20over%2040%20diplomats%2C%20while%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20response%20to%20US%20has%20%E2%80%9Cbeen%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20reasonable%E2%80%9D%2C%20Kaine%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20government%20had%20announced%20that%20it%20had%20set%20up%20a%20committee%20of%20enquiry%20to%20look%20into%20the%20allegations.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Ffirst-visit-pannun-plot-us-accountability-india-silent-publicly%5C%22%3EThe%20United%20States%20recently%20reiterated%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20was%20looking%20at%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20ensure%20accountability%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Clethal%20plotting%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20would%20like%20you%20to%20just%20use%20the%20Indian%20example%20when%20we%E2%80%99re%20dealing%20with%20a%20nation%20that%20we%20have%20such%20strong%20connections%20to.%20We%20have%20military%20connections%2C%20economic%20connections%2C%20connections%20of%20family%20among%20American%20Indian%20diaspora%20community%20in%20the%20United%20States%20which%20is%20such%20an%20important%20part%20of%20who%20we%20are%20as%20a%20as%20a%20country.%20What%20are%20the%20strategies%20you%20suggest%20that%20we%20use%20in%20dealing%20with%20nations%20that%20we%20traditionally%20count%20as%20friends%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbramowitz%20replied%20that%20it%20was%20important%20to%20get%20%E2%80%9Cmore%20information%20about%20India%E2%80%99s%20activities%20in%20democracies%20out%20there%20in%20the%20open%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThat%20strikes%20me%20as%20something%20that%20this%20body%20(Senate%20committee)%20could%20obtain%20from%20you%20know%2C%20sources%20within%20the%20US%20government%2C%20I%20think%20and%E2%80%A6to%20publicise%20as%20much%20as%20you%20can.%20So%2C%20you%20know%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20be%20transparent%20about%20what%E2%80%99s%20going%20on%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20noted%20that%20India%20had%20been%20a%20major%20country%20which%20had%20witnessed%20democratic%20backsliding%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20Pannun%20plot%20could%20be%20a%20consequence%20of%20that.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20see%20two%20broad%20trends%2C%20one%20is%20authoritarian%20countries%20kind%20of%20getting%20stronger.%20But%20you%20also%20see%20backsliding%20among%20established%20democracies%20and%2C%20and%20clearly%20India%20is%20one%20of%20the%20cases%20that%20have%20been%20where%20there%E2%80%99s%20in%20this%20kind%20of%20backsliding.%20So%20the%20kind%20of%20overseas%20activities%20that%20you%20are%20alluding%20to%20is%20also%20part%20of%20the%20democratic%20backsliding%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Abramowitz.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffreedomhouse.org%2Freport%2Ffreedom-world%2F2023%2Fmarking-50-years%23executive-summary%5C%22%3EFreedom%20House%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99s%20annual%20report%20%E2%80%98Freedom%20in%20the%20World%E2%80%99%20had%20downgraded%20India%20to%20a%20%C2%A0%E2%80%9Cpartly%20free%E2%80%9D%20country%20two%20years%20ago.%20India%20had%20then%20dismissed%20the%20report%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ffreedom-house-partly-free-government-reaction%5C%22%3Einaccurate%20and%20distorted%20as%20their%20maps%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701918072000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20230025%2FH20230908138244.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fin-us-senate-hearing-on-transnational-repression-many-questions-on-indias-role-in-pannun-case%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India's%20actions%20were%20listed%20alongside%20other%20cases%20of%20cross-border%20repression%20by%20Washington%E2%80%99s%20perennial%20adversaries%2C%20including%20China%2C%20Russia%20and%20Iran.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%2